The paper deals with dimensionality reduction and clustering of high dimensional data, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions graph smoothness assumptions and convex optimization, which are related to graph theory and optimization, respectively. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed model to corruptions in the data, which is a topic in statistics and signal processing. Therefore, cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible sub-category.
